<D>__{i guess not.}
<C>__{escobar}
<D>__{give you three minutes.}
<C>__{gittes}
<D>__{gee, thanks, lou.}
<A>__{gittes gets out of the car, glances around, goes up the stairs. he looks back down at escobar. gittes rings the bell. he waits. it opens. it's a woman who's not recognizable. she's got the remnants of a black eye.}
<C>__{woman}
<D>__{yes?...}
<A>__{gittes looks past her to curly, the fisherman from the first scene. he's seated at the dinner table with his father, his mother, and his children. curly looks up in surprise.}
<C>__{curly}
<P>__{(happily)}
<D>__{mr. gittes! come in, come in.}
<A>__{gittes enters and closes the door. curly rises and comes over to him, greets him happily.}
